<TEXT>
<P>
 MY DAY: A Tale of Fear, Alienation and Despair by Marvin Heiferman and Carole 
Kismaric. (Chronicle: $6.95 ) This is a truly cynical little book, proving once 
again that good sarcasm can come in small packages. It is a day in 
black-and-white pictures, a really mediocre, middle-class day, complete with 
personal hygiene products, The Office and The Date. Heiferman and Kismaric have 
captured, out of the corners of our eyes, the little details that make up our 
generic, disconnected, product-driven lives. Again, this is not Angst, it is 
despair. Sure, you might laugh, but that is because you are sick, very sick. 
SUSAN SALTER REYNOLDS 
</P>
