<TEXT>
<P>
 AND ONE MORE THING: Of all the holiday promotional items spotted by Pop Eye, 
from key rings to sweat pants, our favorite was a CD-sized booklet from Warner 
Bros. Records. The title: "Holiday Favorites: Recipes from the Family of Warner 
Bros.Records Recording Artists." 
</P>
<P>
 The delicacies range from Madonna's "Krispy Marshmallow Treats" (which 
suspiciously resembles a recipe usually published on a certain cereal box) and 
Biz Markie's tuna casserole -- in which you can use either butter or Cheese 
Whiz -- to a very involved "Enchiladas de Los Lobos" and "Vegetarian Moussaka" 
by k.d. lang (identified as a "Grammy-winning vocalist and vegetable 
enthusiast"). 
</P>
<P>
 And then there's "Lou Reed's X-Mas Recipe": 
</P>
<P>
 "Go to Carnegie Deli and order a hot pastrami sandwich with full sour 
pickles." 
