<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE HOCHMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 RAW NERVE: Nirvana's public wars of words have generally involved high-profile 
opponents -- notably Axl Rose and Eddie Vedder. 
</P>
<P>
 But the latest involves just the kind of folks the band usually supports: 
fellow Seattle rockers Tad. 
</P>
<P>
 It seems Nirvana invited Tad to open nine West Coast shows on its current 
tour, including last week's San Diego and Los Angeles dates. 
</P>
<P>
 But then Tad, the ex-butcher who is lead singer in the band named after 
himself, said something unflattering about Courtney Love -- the wife of 
Nirvana's Kurt Cobain -- to the English pop press. 
</P>
<P>
 Bye-bye Tad. 
</P>
<P>
 Asked about the matter, a publicist for Tad's record company, Giant Records, 
said that Tad's girlfriend and Love "don't get along." 
</P>
<P>
 "Other things contributed, it wasn't solely that," says a Nirvana spokeswoman. 
"But that was the straw that broke the camel's back. You just can't say mean 
things about someone's wife." STEVE HOCHMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
