<LENGTH>
<P>
126 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
STREISAND AND THE TIMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In last Sunday's Film Clips roundup of the year's notable quotes, Chris 
Willman repeated a quote attributed to Barbra Streisand by Spy magazine, in 
reference to celebrities invited to the White House: "Why Sharon Stone? She 
doesn't know anything about policy." Our item prompted the following response:  
</P>
<P>
 The quote which Chris Willman attributed to me in his Sunday article was false 
and ridiculous. But what really offended me was that the Los Angeles Times 
would stoop to quoting Spy magazine as its source without seeking to verify 
such an offensive statement. 
</P>
<P>
 However, that pales against your paper's tabloid-like presentation of the 
allegations against the President of the United States. 
</P>
<P>
 BARBRA STREISAND 
</P>
<P>
 Las Vegas 
</P>
