<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: WALNUT; SENIORS SOUGHT FOR PATROLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is recruiting senior citizens for a volunteer patrol program with the 
city and the Walnut sheriff's station. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers will be issued uniforms and will use a city-owned car and car phone 
to perform various patrol duties assigned by deputies, including vacation house 
checks, park patrol and construction site checks. 
</P>
<P>
 People 50 or older who can work one six-hour shift each week are encouraged to 
apply. Volunteers must have a valid driver's license, undergo a background and 
fingerprint check, have no felony convictions and pass an oral interview.  
</P>
<P>
 To volunteer or for more information, call Deputy Frank Girard at (909) 
595-2264 or Rob Wishner at Walnut City Hall, (909) 595-7543. 
</P>
