<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: REGION; WATER COMPANY WARNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reports of people posing as water company workers have prompted the San 
Gabriel Valley Water Co. to alert its 45,000 customers to beware of anyone 
asking to enter a home to inspect the plumbing. 
</P>
<P>
 The alert followed complaints last year about thefts by people who represented 
themselves as water company employees to enter houses. 
</P>
<P>
 The El Monte-based water supplier is notifying its customers that normally a 
water company employee would not ask to enter a house. This would happen only 
if a customer had previously contacted the company. 
</P>
<P>
 Also company officials said any questions about whether someone is an employee 
can be directed to the customer service office at (818) 448-6183. 
</P>
<P>
 The water company serves El Monte, Rosemead, San Gabriel, Hacienda Heights, La 
Puente, Baldwin Park, Whittier and Montebello. 
</P>
