<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ARCADIA; HOSPITAL PRESIDENT SELECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The board of directors of Methodist Hospital of Southern California has 
selected Dennis M. Lee, a 43-year-old Monrovia resident, as the new president 
of the Huntington Drive hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee will be responsible for the 347-bed facility near the Santa Anita Park 
racetrack and will also serve as president of Methodist Hospital Foundation, 
the board announced. 
</P>
<P>
 He will replace Frederick C. Meyer, president since 1985. Meyer will become 
chief operating officer of Southern California Healthcare, formed when 
Methodist Hospital and Pasadena's Huntington Memorial Hospital affiliated in 
December, 1992. Meyer will oversee operations at both facilities and handle 
corporate affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 Methodist Hospital hired Lee in April, 1991, as chief operating officer. For 
the past year, he has served as executive vice president and administrator of 
the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee is on the board of the Arcadia Chamber of Commerce and is vice chairman of 
the Arcadia branch of the American Heart Assn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
