<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: COVINA, WEST COVINA; 2 HOSPITALS TALKING MERGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The boards of two San Gabriel Valley hospitals -- Queen of the Valley in West 
Covina and Inter-Community Medical Center in Covina -- are discussing the 
possibility of merging. 
</P>
<P>
 On Dec. 20, both boards adopted a non-binding agreement to merge the two 
hospitals within 120 days.The resolutions pave the way for further 
negotiations. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials from both hospitals said they are considering a merger as a way to 
remain competitive in the changing health-care environment. 
</P>
<P>
 Queen of the Valley had been involved in affiliation discussions with Southern 
California Healthcare Systems, which is made up of Huntington Memorial Hospital 
and Methodist Hospital of Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 Those two hospitals have agreed to end discussions to allow Queen of the 
Valley and Inter-Community hospital to proceed with negotiations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
