<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA CORNER; FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SAN FRANCISCO -- The San Francisco Sports and Boat Show brings about 600 
exhibitors to the Cow Palace, Jan. 14-23. Noon-10 p.m. weekdays, 11 a.m.-10 
p.m. Saturdays, and 11 a.m.-7 p.m. Sundays.Geneva and Santos streets in Daly 
City. $6, general; $3, kids; $3 for seniors during the week. (415) 931-2500. 
BLYTHE -- Strummers, pickers and fiddlers gather for the seventh annual 
Colorado River Country Music Festival, Jan. 21-23 at the Colorado River Country 
Fairgrounds, two miles east of Blythe on Riverside Drive. Information on 
tickets, camping or competition registration: (800) 445-0541. SAN DIEGO -- 
Marvel at the migration of California gray whales during Cabrillo National 
Monument's Whale Watch Weekend, Jan. 22-23. Exhibits, lectures and a children's 
program are planned. All day both days, starting at 10 a.m. At the end of 
Catalina Boulevard (California 209), on the southern end of Point Loma. (619) 
557-5450. HEALDSBURG -- Taste your way through the Alexander, Dry Creek and 
Russian River valleys in Sonoma County at the second annual Winter Wineland, 
Feb. 4-6. More than 25 bed and breakfast inns host special wine tastings and 
dinners Friday night. On Saturday-Sunday, more than 45 wineries host special 
activities, 11 a.m.-4 p.m. Tickets for self-guided wine tours: $15. Tickets 
(with a wine glass included) available at participating wineries and inns. 
(707) 433-6782. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
