<HEADLINE>
<P>
FILM CLIPS / A LOOK INSIDE HOLLYWOOD AND THE MOVIES.: HUNKY HOLIDAYS FROM 
HOLLYWOOD: SEX SYMBOLS LIGHT UP THE SCREEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARSHALL FINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hollywood used to crank out starlets by the bushel but, these days, it's the 
male counterpart that seems to be in abundance. Sex symbolism is in the eye of 
the beholder, but one doesn't have to look very far to see that, in the current 
crop of Christmas movies, the hunks out-number the starlets by a wide margin. 
Call them the boy toys of winter.  
</P>
<P>
 And while youth will be served, so will their older counterparts in the 
movie-going audience. So we make note of the plethora of male pulchritude 
adorning multiplex screens, even as we tip a hat to the robust senior division 
as well. YOUNG HUNKS 
