<HEADLINE>
<P>
CUBAN REFUGEES A RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A record number of Cuban refugees floated to Florida in 1993. Last year, 3,656 
Cubans reached Florida by boat, up 43% from 2,557 in 1992, Coast Guard Petty 
Officer Chris Whitlock said Saturday. It was the largest exodus since the 1980 
Mariel boat lift, which saw 125,000 Cubans flee to Florida. 
</P>
