<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOUSE PAINTER HERO IN FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A house painter grabbed his ladder and battled heavy smoke to rescue three 
people from a burning apartment building's third floor and help firefighters 
save a fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 The rescuer, Ronald Ford, 37, was treated at a hospital for smoke inhalation 
and released. Ford was visiting his brother in an apartment building next door 
when the fire broke out Friday. 
</P>
