<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIVE ARRESTED IN BOTCHED ROBBERY, HOSTAGE INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Several people were taken hostage in a clothing store after a botched robbery, 
and one customer was wounded before all hostages went free, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Five people were arrested in the Friday evening incident, which unfolded only 
a few blocks from the Times Square New Year's Eve throngs. The police 
department's negotiating team persuaded the men to surrender about two hours 
after the incident began. 
</P>
