<TYPE>
<P>
Wild Art 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA010294-0160 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 000366 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
January 2, 1994, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 5; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
363 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENVIRONMENT: NOTES ABOUT YOUR SURROUNDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Post-Christmas Bird Count Field Trip -- The Sea & Sage chapter of the National 
Audubon Society will hold its post-Christmas Bird Count specialties field trip 
on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The purpose of the annual event is to look for the highlights of the birds 
spotted during the chapter's two local Christmas Bird Counts. The northeastern 
count was held Dec. 19 and the coastal count is being held today. 
</P>
<P>
 A schedule for the day will be distributed at the start of the trip, which 
begins at 8 a.m. at Huntington Central Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The trip group will meet at the park's Slater Street parking lot. To reach it, 
take the San Diego Freeway to the Golden West Street exit, go south. Turn left 
at Slater and the park and parking lot will be on the right. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who take the trip are asked to wear comfortable shoes and be prepared to 
get wet feet from walking on wet grass. It is also suggested that those 
participating bring a warm jacket. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants are also asked to bring an Orange County map to help find the 
other birding locations. The length of the trip will depend upon how many 
different locations in which the highlighted birds were spotted. The trip will 
probably last the entire day. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Sea & Sage chapter office at (714) 261-7963. 
</P>
<P>
 Marsh Bird Walk -- The Sea & Sage chapter of the National Audubon Society is 
hosting monthly bird-watching walks for adults and younger bird-watchers at the 
San Joaquin Wildlife Sanctuary, which is next to its Audubon House. The next 
walk for adults will be Jan. 9 at 9 a.m. The next walk for 11- to 16-year-olds 
will be Jan. 15 at 8:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Each of the walks will be led by Chris Obaditch. 
</P>
<P>
 Advance reservations are not necessary. Beginning and advanced bird-watchers 
are welcome. 
</P>
<P>
 Binoculars will be provided for those who do not have their own. 
</P>
<P>
 To reach the Audubon House, where the walk will start, take the San Diego 
Freeway to the Jamboree Road exit, head south. Turn left at Michelson Drive, 
and then right at the second signal onto Irvine Ranch Water District property. 
Follow the paved road and "Duck Club" signs to the house. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Sea & Sage chapter office at (714) 261-7963. 
</P>
</TEXT>
