<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIKE SMITH GETS OFF TO A FAST START AT CALDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Smith, who broke the record for stakes victories by a jockey in a year 
with 62 in 1993, had two at Calder Race Course on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 He rode favored Trampoli to victory in the $150,000 La Prevoyante Handicap and 
Take Me Out won the $100,000 Tropical Park Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
 Trampoli covered 1 1/2 miles on turf in 2:28 in beating Putthepowdertoit by 2 
1/2 lengths, with Adoryphar another 1 3/4 lengths back. 
</P>
<P>
 Trampoli paid $4.80, $3.20 and $2.40. Putthepowdertoit paid $4.20 and $3.60 
and Adoryphar returned $4.80. 
</P>
