<HEADLINE>
<P>
THIEF TAKES SNOW SHOVEL AS MAN CLEARS DRIVEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man clearing snow from his driveway was robbed of his shovel at gunpoint, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Give me the shovel. I need the shovel right now," the robber said after he 
stopped his car Thursday night, jumped out and grabbed the shovel, Woodbridge 
Police Detective Joe Joraskie said. 
</P>
<P>
 After a tugging match, the robber pulled out a pistol and aimed it at the 
victim, who surrendered the shovel. The robber then handed it to a passenger, 
got back into the car and drove off, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
