<HEADLINE>
<P>
STOWAWAY ON RIO-ROME FLIGHT DIES IN CARGO BAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A young Brazilian man was found dead inside a jetliner's cargo bay Saturday 
after sneaking onto a flight from Rio de Janeiro to Rome, airport officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of the 20-year-old man was discovered by a ground crew after the 
Varig airline flight landed at Rome's main airport. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, from Rio de Janeiro, was exposed to extremely low temperatures and 
apparently froze to death, the officials said. The cargo area where he hid also 
had little oxygen, they added. 
</P>
