<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY OFFICIALS NEGLECT A DANGEROUS EYESORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * It is upsetting to see how continually callous the L.A. Department of 
Building and Safety is when it comes to Valley concerns. The area on the south 
side of Ventura Boulevard, between Woodman Avenue and Ventura Canyon Avenue, 
has been an eyesore and a danger to the community now for more than three 
years, but (the department) chooses to take no action. 
</P>
<P>
 It defiles the very essence of the community. It's a graffiti writer's nightly 
challenge, requiring constant vigilance by a committee to wipe out their 
scribblings. The Fire Department is often called to put out fires created by 
individuals who are living there. I personally have seen dope pushers openly 
selling their wares in the areas behind the buildings. 
</P>
<P>
 But to the Building and Safety Department, none of this matters. I wonder 
whether it would make a difference if one of those worthies lived in the area? 
</P>
<P>
 ALFRED E.F. STERN 
</P>
<P>
 Sherman Oaks 
</P>
