<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOKA EXPANSION PLANS DESERVE A FAIR REVIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I was amazed to see the Sierra Club, of all organizations, wrongly criticize 
the Soka University project as one of the worst developments in the area. This 
is the same group that did not stand up to, and even praised, Ahmanson, Micor, 
Baldwin and a lot of other developments that are incredibly more destructive. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ahmanson project is grading 400 times more earth than Soka. Micor, which 
is right across the street from the campus, is removing five acres of native 
wetlands. It is also cutting into a wildlife corridor. Baldwin is removing 30 
times as many oak trees as Soka. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santa Monica Mountains Conservancy, which has gleefully supported all of 
these projects, has consistently demonstrated its double standard when it comes 
to Soka University. 
</P>
<P>
 The university is providing a greater percentage of open space than even the 
Ahmanson project is setting aside, and in Soka's case the public won't have to 
pay for it. I think that the public is starting to see what the Conservancy is 
really up to now. 
</P>
<P>
 ALEXIS BYFUGLIN 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
