<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROSE BOWL / WISCONSIN BADGERS 21, UCLA BRUINS 16; TO ERR IS BRUIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UCLA set a Rose Bowl record with five fumbles. A look at the costliest of the 
Bruin mistakes: 
</P>
<P>
 TURNOVERS THAT LED TO SCORES 
</P>
<P>
 * 9:04 remaining, second quarter: J.J. Stokes fumbles on UCLA 32, recovered by 
Lamark Shackerford.Eight plays later, Brent Moss scores on a one-yard run. 
Score: Wisconsin 14, UCLA 3. 
</P>
<P>
 * 12:15 remaining, fourth quarter: Ricky Davis fumbles at UCLA 34, recovered 
by Mike Thompson. Five plays later, Darrell Bevell scores on a 21-yard run. 
Score: Wisconsin 21, UCLA 10. 
</P>
<P>
 DRIVE-KILLERS 
</P>
<P>
 * 10:47 remaining, second quarter: Wayne Cook's pass, intended for Kevin 
Jordan, is intercepted at the UCLA 44 by Jeff Messenger. Score: Wisconsin 7, 
UCLA 3. 
</P>
<P>
 * 12:13 remaining, third quarter: Cook fumbles while sacked for four-yard 
loss, recovered by Thompson on Wisconsin 8. Score: Wisconsin 14, UCLA 3. 
</P>
<P>
 * 3:39 remaining, third quarter: Cook fumbles while sacked for four-yard loss, 
recovered by Henry Searcy at Wisconsin 37. Score: Wisconsin 14, UCLA 3. 
</P>
<P>
 * 8:46 remaining, fourth quarter: Jordan fumbles after 12-yard reception, 
recovered by Scott Nelson at UCLA 49. Personal foul penalty on Badgers places 
ball at Wisconsin 36. Score: Wisconsin 21 UCLA 10. 
</P>
