<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUBSIDIZED HOUSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Times is to be commended for its editorial "There Is Room at the Inn, 
Alas" (Dec. 21).It is a tragedy that general relief clients have seen their 
checks reduced from $341 to $293 and then to the current $212 over the past 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 As you mention, "That is not enough to rent a room, unless the recipient is 
lucky enough to get one of the few (hotel rooms) subsidized by the Community 
Redevelopment Agency." Luckily we just reopened the La Jolla Hotel, which was 
rehabilitated with agency funds. We now have 49 newly renovated rooms for rent 
to general relief clients for $180 per month. 
</P>
<P>
 ANDY RAUBESON, Executive Director 
</P>
<P>
 SRO Housing, Los Angeles 
