<HEADLINE>
<P>
'93/'94 YEAR-END REVIEW AND OUTLOOK; YEAR-END SPECIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Today's Business section is a special issue looking back at 1993 and ahead to 
1994, in both the economy and the financial markets. 
</P>
<P>
 Regular Sunday features will return next week. 
</P>
<P>
 The expanded financial tables in today's section are annual performance 
summaries for stocks and mutual funds. They take the place of the weekly 
tables. Markets columnist Tom Petruno has put together a user-friendly summary 
of the market year, D8. A special guide to understanding and using the mutual 
fund charts is on D11. 
</P>
<P>
 If you invest -- or plan to -- today's section can be a valuable resource. Use 
it to evaluate your holdings' performance in 1993 against market averages and 
to decide on the best opportunities for 1994. 
</P>
<P>
 Today's features on the economy's prospects, meanwhile, can help guide your 
personal and professional business decisions in the year ahead. 
</P>
<P>
 On Wednesday, the Business section will publish a special report on stock 
mutual funds, ranking he best- and worst-performing funds of 1993 and assessing 
the fund outlook for 1994. 
</P>
