<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIFT HELPS CLINIC TAKE NEW PATIENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Clinica Para las Americas, the largest nonprofit primary health care clinic 
serving Pico-Union and Westlake, has received a $50,000 shot in the arm thanks 
to a private donation disbursed through RLA, formerly known as Rebuild LA. 
</P>
<P>
 The donation will be used to hire a part-time physician, fund medications and 
laboratory tests and expand its services to an estimated 3,000 additional 
patients.The clinic had been forced to refuse new patients because of its 
overwhelming case load. 
</P>
<P>
 The clinic, founded in 1989, had about 11,000 patients this year and thousands 
more received HIV tests, health and parenting education and counseling through 
the clinic's community outreach program, said Leslie Gallagher, the clinic's 
development director. 
</P>
<P>
 The clinic is at 318 S. Alvarado St. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 484-8434. 
</P>
